/-
We prove that for any $C>0$, there exists a constant $K$ such that there are infinitely many triples $(a,b,n)$ with $a+b > n + C \log n$ and the denominator of $n!/(a!b!)$ being $K$-smooth. This answers the Erdős-Graham-Ruzsa-Straus problem affirmatively.
-/

